(Agentic Nexus - Quick Start Guide) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 766 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 752 Tm
(Welcome to Agentic Nexus, your AI agent builder and workflow automation platform.) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 738 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 724 Tm
(Chapter 1: Getting Started) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 710 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 696 Tm
(Agentic Nexus allows you to create AI agents, test them interactively, build multi-step workflows, and monitor execution with human-in-the-loop controls.) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 682 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 668 Tm
(To get started:) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 654 Tm
(1. Navigate to New Agent in the sidebar) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 640 Tm
(2. Give your agent a name and select a model \(OpenAI, Anthropic, or Mock\)) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 626 Tm
(3. Write system instructions that define the agent behavior) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 612 Tm
(4. Toggle tools like Web Search, Code Interpreter, Memory, and Knowledge) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 598 Tm
(5. Set parameters like temperature, max tokens, and top-p) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 584 Tm
(6. Click Deploy to activate the agent) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 570 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 556 Tm
(Chapter 2: Testing Agents) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 542 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 528 Tm
(The Test Console provides a real-time chat interface:) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 514 Tm
(- Messages stream via WebSocket for low-latency responses) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 500 Tm
(- Enable Run with Tools to allow the agent to use configured tools) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 486 Tm
(- Enable Human-in-the-Loop to approve or reject tool calls before execution) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 472 Tm
(- View token usage and latency statistics after each response) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 458 Tm
(- Use the curl snippet to reproduce test runs programmatically) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 444 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 430 Tm
(Chapter 3: Building Workflows) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 416 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 402 Tm
(Workflows let you chain multiple agents into automated pipelines:) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 388 Tm
(- Each workflow consists of ordered steps) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 374 Tm
(- Steps can be assigned to specific agents or run as orchestrator messages) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 360 Tm
(- Steps can require human approval before execution) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 346 Tm
(- Triggers include manual, scheduled \(cron\), webhook, and event-based) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 332 Tm
(- The Run Console shows step-by-step progress with streaming logs) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 318 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 304 Tm
(Chapter 4: Knowledge Base \(RAG\)) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 290 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 276 Tm
(The Knowledge feature enables Retrieval-Augmented Generation:) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 262 Tm
(- Drop PDF files into the knowledge/pdfs directory) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 248 Tm
(- Run the ingestion script to parse and chunk documents) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 234 Tm
(- Enable the Knowledge tool on your agents) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 220 Tm
(- Agents will search the knowledge base and include relevant citations) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 206 Tm
(- Supports BM25 local search \(no API keys\) and OpenAI embeddings) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 192 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 178 Tm
(Chapter 5: Providers and Models) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 164 Tm
() Tj
1 0 0 1 40 150 Tm
(Agentic Nexus supports multiple LLM providers:) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 136 Tm
(- OpenAI: gpt-4o-mini, gpt-4o, o3-mini) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 122 Tm
(- Anthropic: claude-3-haiku, claude-3-sonnet, claude-3.5-sonnet) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 108 Tm
(- Mock: Three mock models for offline development and testing) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 94 Tm
(- Set your API keys in the .env file) Tj
1 0 0 1 40 80 Tm
(- The Mock provider requires no keys and returns simulated responses) Tj
